<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1660,1831]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1660,1684]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
O. Lonsdale (pers. comm.) confirmed that 
<taxonomicName box="[786,1059,1660,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutiseta">
<emphasis box="[786,1059,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Allometopon hirsutiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1373,1660,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Sobarocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1373,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Sobarocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[375,473,1696,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
female deposited in Vienna (
<collectionCode box="[813,912,1696,1720]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">NHMW</collectionCode>
): that is, it has the characteristic cephalic and thoracic chaetotaxies and wing venation (cell bm and M 
<number box="[794,802,1747,1761]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
ratio), and a plumose arista. This generic reassignment should be attributed to Lonsdale in Sasakawa (herein).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
